      "qid": "SRCH-NI-138-1",
      "question": "section 138 negotiable instruments cheque dishonour",
      "answer": "Section 138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881, pertains to the dishonour of a cheque [E1, E2]. A case may involve the dishonour of a cheque issued for loan repayment [E2].\n\nUpon the dishonour of a cheque, Clause (b) of the proviso to Section 138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act requires the payee or holder to make a demand for payment by giving written notice to the drawer of the cheque [E4]. This notice must be given upon the return of the cheque as unpaid [E4]. For instance, a cheque dishonoured on 2-7-1996 was followed by a notice dated 16-7-1996, which was within the time prescribed under Clause (b) of the proviso to Section 138 [E4].\n\nIt is important to note that the cause of action for an offence under Section 138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act does not arise merely by issuing a notice of dishonour of a cheque [E7]. Proceedings under Section 138 can lead to a petitioner being summoned to face trial [E5].",
